    <div class="card-info" id="cardInfo">
    <h2>Kitasato Shibasaburo</h2>
    <p><strong>Lifetime:</strong> 1853–1931</p>
    <p><strong>Title:</strong> First to Isolate Clostridium tetani and a Pioneer of Serology</p>
    <p><strong>Achievements:</strong> Kitasato Shibasaburo (1853–1931) was a prominent Japanese physician and bacteriologist renowned for his groundbreaking discoveries in infectious diseases. He is best known for his work on tetanus, diphtheria, and the bubonic plague. Kitasato's key contributions include the isolation of the tetanus bacillus in pure culture, the development of serum therapy for tetanus and diphtheria, and the independent discovery of the causative agent of the bubonic plague, Yersinia pestis.</p>
    <p><strong>Legacy:</strong> His legacy extends beyond these discoveries, as he established the Institute for Infectious Diseases in Japan, which later became the National Institute for Infectious Diseases. He also founded the Kitasato Institute, a private research center that continues to contribute to medical research today. Kitasato's work laid the foundation for modern bacteriology and immunology, and his contributions to public health continue to impact medical practices worldwide.</p>
</div>


    <script>
        const card = document.getElementById('gameCard');
        const cardInfo = document.getElementById('cardInfo');

        card.addEventListener('click', () => {
            card.classList.toggle('is-flipped');
            cardInfo.classList.toggle('visible');
        });
    </script>

